<HEADLINE>
FT  24 DEC 92 / Finance and the Family: C &amp; G rate cut - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CHELTENHAM &amp; Gloucester is reducing the interest paid on its London Deposit
postal account from January 2. In October, C &amp; G promised to guarantee the
rate for three months. The new rates represent a drop of about 2 percentage
points. They will be 7 per cent gross annual interest on balances on Pounds
5,000-Pounds 9,999; 7.5 per cent on Pounds 10,000-Pounds 24,999 and 8 per
cent on sums over Pounds 25,000.
The Moneyfacts table 'Highest Rates for Your Money' will next appear in our
January 2 issue.
</TEXT>
