FT  23 DEC 92 / US NBER says recession ended in March 1991
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL PROWSE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The US National Bureau of Economic Research yesterday declared the recession
ended in March 1991, eight months after it began in July 1990, Michael
Prowse reports. It delayed its decision until yesterday's figures from the
Commerce Department confirmed that the economy had surpassed its
pre-recession peak. The figures showed real gross domestic product growth at
an annual rate of 3.4 per cent in the third quarter compared with a previous
estimate of 3.9 per cent.
