<TEXT>
The brother-in-law of former Mexican president Luis Echeverria has been
found guilty of conspiring to murder Mr Enrique Camarena, an official of the
US Drug Enforcement Agency (DEA), in a case that led to a sharp dispute
between Mexico and the US, Damian Fraser writes from Mexico City.
Mr Ruben Zuno Acre was tried with the Mexican doctor Mr Humberto Alvarez
Machain, who had been kidnapped by agents working for the DEA in 1990 to
face charges in the US. The case against Dr Alvarez Machain was dismissed by
the judge last week. The kidnapping of Mr Alvarez Machain and subsequent
trial infuriated the Mexican government.
