<TEXT>
US SMALLER Companies Investment Trust, which floated on the main market in
1991, is raising another Pounds 40m via a placing and open offer.
The trust is managed by Wellington Management International, part of the US
investment group Wellington, and its share price has performed well since
launch. Shares were trading at 129p yesterday morning, compared to a launch
price of 100p and the warrants (initially offered on a one-for-five basis)
