</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
JAPANESE prosecutors have decided not to charge60 ruling party MPs who
received shares in an illegal Y500m (Pounds 2.65m) donation from Tokyo
Sagawa Kyubin, a scandal-tainted trucking company.
The prosecutors' decision appears to close the case book on the Tokyo Sagawa
scandal, which has already seen the resignation of Mr Shin Kanemaru, the
Liberal Democratic party godfather, and highlighted the links between
leading politicians and gangsters.
Mr Kanemaru admitted receiving the Y500m from Tokyo Sagawa, which had sought
to cultivate political contacts, but the 60 MPs refused to identify
themselves as having received funds, fearing they would be charged with
violating the Political Funds Control Law.
